1. What are Java loops?
Loops allow a block of code to run multiple times until a condition is met.
Types:
for loop
while loop
do-while loop
Enhanced for-each loop


2. What is enhanced for-loop?
The enhanced for-loop (or for-each loop) is used to iterate over arrays or collections without using an index.
for (String name : names) {
    System.out.println(name);
}
It’s read-only (you can’t modify the collection while iterating directly).


3. How do you handle multiple user inputs?
You can use the Scanner class and read inputs in a loop.
Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
for (int i = 0; i < 5; i++) {
    System.out.print("Enter a number: ");
    int num = sc.nextInt();
}
Or read until a stop condition.


4. How is a switch-case different from if-else?
if-else: Works for ranges, conditions, and logical operations.
switch-case: Best for fixed values (int, char, String, enum).
switch(day) {
    case "Monday": System.out.println("Workday"); break;
    default: System.out.println("Invalid");
}


5. What are collections in Java?
Collections are data structures in the java.util package used to store, manipulate, and retrieve groups of objects.
Examples: List, Set, Queue, Map.


6. What is ArrayList?
A resizable array in Java.
Allows duplicates and maintains insertion order.
Belongs to java.util.
ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add("Apple");


7. How to iterate using iterators?
ArrayList<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
list.add("A"); list.add("B");
Iterator<String> it = list.iterator();
while (it.hasNext()) {
    System.out.println(it.next());
}
Iterator allows safe removal of elements while looping.


8. What is a Map?
A Map<K, V> stores key-value pairs.
Keys are unique.
Examples: HashMap, TreeMap, LinkedHashMap.
Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
map.put("John", 25);


9. How to sort a list?
Collections.sort(list); // Ascending
Collections.sort(list, Collections.reverseOrder()); // Descending


10. How to shuffle elements?
Collections.shuffle(list);
Randomizes the order of elements in the list.